1
00:02:52,200 --> 00:02:55,795
- (men banging)
- Kleinman, open up!

2
00:02:55,920 --> 00:02:58,992
- Kleinman!
- We know you're in there!

3
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:01,076
Kleinman!

4
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:06,076
Come on, Kleinman!

5
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:10,234
l'm coming! l'm coming!

6
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:12,271
Kleinman!

7
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:16,473
- For God's sake, Kleinman. Are you deaf?
- What do you mean? What's going on?

8
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:18,556
- We need you. Get dressed.
- Why?

9
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:21,069
- Don't play ignorant.
- l was in a deep sleep.

10
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:24,397
- We expect the killer to strike tonight.
- What killer?

11
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:26,317
- The strangler.
- What strangler?

12
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:30,877
The maniac who killed Eisler's son
and choked Jensen with the piano wire.

13
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:34,993
Jensen? The... the...
the big night watchman?

14
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:37,554
That's right. Took him from behind.

15
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:41,275
Crept up, got him by the throat.
He was blue when we found him.

16
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:44,039
Saliva frozen down the corner
of his mouth.

17
00:03:45,040 --> 00:03:47,998
Well, look, l've gotta be up early
tomorrow for work, so...

18
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:52,511
Don't play dumb. Tonight's a foggy night.
He always strikes in the fog.

19
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:56,110
Yeah, but, you see, this is a very
busy time for me in my firm.

20
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:59,073
l'm in competition for
a promotion with Simon Carr.

21
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:02,317
Don't you know no one
can walk the streets at night?

22
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:05,671
And the Quilty sisters
were killed in their own home...

23
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:08,997
..because they didn't lock the door,
throats cut from ear to ear.

24
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:12,590
- You said he was a strangler.
- Does it matter how he kills?!

25
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:15,598
What is he getting so angry for? OK, OK.

26
00:04:15,720 --> 00:04:18,234
- There's no motive?
- So you know about it.

27
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:21,318
Well, you know, l hear,
now and then, a drib and drab.

28
00:04:21,440 --> 00:04:23,954
- He hears what he wants to hear.
- Get dressed.

29
00:04:24,080 --> 00:04:26,799
- This is police business.
- They've had their chance.

30
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:29,309
- We're taking it into our own hands.
- That's scary.

31
00:04:29,440 --> 00:04:32,273
- You're one of us, aren't you?
- l'm definitely one of you.

32
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:34,914
- What do you want me to do?
- We have a plan to trap him.

33
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:37,918
- What kind of plan?
- lt's Hacker's. He should tell it.

34
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:40,793
You'll find out your assignment.
Get dressed.

35
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:44,117
- What do you mean?
- Meet you downstairs in five minutes.

36
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:46,515
My theory is, it's someone
that we all know,...

37
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:49,074
..someone we work next to
or go to church with.

38
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:51,589
He lurks in the shadows,
waiting to pounce.

39
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:55,838
But, you see, l was in a deep sleep,
so... so l was...

40
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:58,671
What is this plan? How can l be of help?

41
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:01,360
Kleinman. Kleinman. ln, in, in, in.

42
00:05:03,760 --> 00:05:05,716
Kleinman, here.

43
00:05:05,840 --> 00:05:07,876
- l brought you some pepper.
- Pepper?

44
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:12,232
l overheard everything. lf you're caught
by the maniac, blow pepper in his eyes.

45
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:15,875
Very good. l'll ward him off with
a seasoning. This is ridiculous!

46
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:18,992
- l'm petrified. l'm not gonna go out...
- Be a man, Kleinman.

47
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:23,352
Be a man? Suddenly, in the middle of the
night, l gotta put on a suit and a tie and...

48
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:27,439
What do you need a tie for? You're
going to hunt for a homicidal maniac.

49
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:30,757
Do l know who l'll run into out there?
What if l see my boss?

50
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:32,836
Mr Paulsen is funny that way.

51
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:36,475
There's a big competition between me
and Simon Carr for this promotion.

52
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:40,479
What are you killing yourself for?
What does it mean? An extra few dollars?

53
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:43,751
No, l told you. lt isn't the money.
l wanna amount to something.

54
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:47,429
Why should Carr get the promotion?
Because he takes Paulsen to dinner?

55
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:51,439
You're too frightened of Mr Paulsen.
You cringe in front of him like a worm.

56
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:54,279
Well, he makes me nervous.
And l don't cringe.

57
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:58,473
- Calling him ''Your Majesty'' is cringing.
- Stop it. l don't like this.

58
00:05:58,600 --> 00:06:01,990
l don't wanna go out. l was in a nice
warm bed. Suddenly l'm part of a plan.

59
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:05,590
Come to your senses and marry me.
You could tell your boss to stuff it...

60
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:09,110
- ..and you'd own half of this whole place.
- l'm not gonna marry you.

61
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:11,913
- l have a fiancée.
- Some fiancée.

62
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:14,918
Eve wants you for an ornament,
if you get the promotion.

63
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:17,759
Don't talk about Eve.
l don't wanna discuss this.

64
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:21,759
- Eve is a lovely creature.
- Eve treats you like scum. Be careful.

65
00:06:21,880 --> 00:06:26,396
l'd hate for them to find you in an alley
with your throat slit from ear to ear.

66
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:29,876
Don't worry about that.
He mostly strangles.

67
00:06:44,880 --> 00:06:47,235
Gee, it´s empty.

68
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:49,669
Where is everybody?

69
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:52,473
They´re supposed to be here.

70
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:54,716
Where the hell´d they go?

71
00:06:54,840 --> 00:06:57,195
The street´s so desolate.

72
00:06:57,320 --> 00:06:58,355
(cat screeches)

73
00:06:58,480 --> 00:07:04,350
l don´t like this. l wanna get back into bed.
l can´t do that, though.

74
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:09,031
lfsomething goes wrong with their plan,
they´ll say it´s my fault.

75
00:07:10,320 --> 00:07:11,230
Why me?

76
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:45,069
l'm an artist. Every town we played in,
l'd get huge laughs. And here, nothing.

77
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:48,670
l mean, no one comes, and the few
that do just sit there stonefaced.

78
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:52,588
l know. l was very little appreciated
myself. None of us were.

79
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:56,315
- Your specialty is quite different to mine.
- l don't know about that.

80
00:07:56,440 --> 00:08:01,116
You can tell a lot about an audience by
how they respond to a sword-swallower.

81
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:06,234
Nothing is more terrifying than attempting
to make people laugh, and failing.

82
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:09,079
Why do we put up with it?
When we pull out tomorrow,...

83
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:11,998
..why don't we just tell
Danzig we're quitting?

84
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:14,793
- To do what?
- Well, settle down.

85
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:19,277
Where we don't have to travel all the time,
where it's not such a gruelling life.

86
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:22,710
Get married, you know.
Live like other people.

87
00:08:22,840 --> 00:08:26,196
We're not like other people. We're artists.

88
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:28,880
With great talent comes responsibility.

89
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:32,834
But it would be so nice.
You could find a job someplace.

90
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:36,953
Doing what? Collecting other people's
refuse? Sweeping the streets?

91
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:40,629
Of course not! No, you're clever.
Somebody'd give you an opportunity.

92
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:44,833
But l have a rare opportunity now,
to make people laugh.

93
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:47,428
To make them forget their sad lives.

94
00:08:47,560 --> 00:08:50,916
Listen, it's not my fault
that this stupid travelling show...

95
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:53,759
..is completely mismanaged.

96
00:08:53,880 --> 00:08:59,000
l'm sure Danzig steals...
every cent of profit.

97
00:08:59,120 --> 00:09:03,159
- l wanna have a baby.
- We're going to, but not right now.

98
00:09:03,280 --> 00:09:07,637
A family? That's death to the artist.
l need peace and quiet.

99
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:11,355
l mean, you know, my mind, it's funny...

100
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:14,358
lt's just constantly filled with...

101
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:18,712
..new routines, ideas, gags,
brilliant and creative twists.

102
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:21,877
Why don't you tell the truth?
You don't want to get married.

103
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:25,515
So you can play cards and flirt
with all the adoring ladies.

104
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:27,835
- That's not true.
- Oh, yes, it is.

105
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:30,520
l have to make a name for myself first.

106
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:32,995
- (sobs)
- We will get marr...

107
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:37,672
- l love you.
- No. You keep promising.

108
00:09:37,800 --> 00:09:41,554
But soon it's gonna be too late
for me to have a baby.

109
00:09:43,160 --> 00:09:45,628
Don't cry.

110
00:09:45,760 --> 00:09:48,752
- Listen, l'll talk to Danzig.
- You don't mean it.

111
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:52,270
l do mean it. Stop.
You know l can't stand that.

112
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:54,630
Don't cry.

113
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:26,273
(woman) The audience
was too quiet tonight.

114
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:28,709
l felt sorry for you.

115
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:31,832
You're the only one they seem to like.

116
00:10:31,960 --> 00:10:34,872
Yeah, but l have my little tricks
for seducing them.

117
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,956
Yes.

118
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:40,952
What are you doing
wandering around out here?

119
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:43,640
l was on my way to speak to Danzig.

120
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:47,476
Like lrish whiskey?

121
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:52,196
Yes, but my doctor says
it's very bad for my stomach.

122
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:53,389
Oh.

123
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:55,875
That's too bad.

124
00:10:57,840 --> 00:10:59,796
But, uh...

125
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:03,040
lt's... probably relaxing.

126
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:15,311
The most voluptuous woman
in the circus.

127
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:19,558
lt would be my luck
she'd be married to the strongman.

128
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:23,673
Don't worry about Peter.
He's had a gallon of this already.

129
00:11:24,680 --> 00:11:26,636
(snoring)

130
00:11:26,760 --> 00:11:30,639
(clown) You know, sometimes when
you're up on the high wire, l look at you.

131
00:11:30,760 --> 00:11:32,716
You look so...

132
00:11:34,640 --> 00:11:36,596
What?

133
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:38,676
Edible.

134
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:43,640
How hungry are you now?

135
00:11:43,760 --> 00:11:48,231
l'm always famished
after a performance. And you?

136
00:11:48,360 --> 00:11:51,113
l can never sleep on an empty stomach.

137
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:54,958
Do you have a taste for anything special?

138
00:11:56,040 --> 00:12:00,192
l'm not fussy. l eat
what you put in front of me.

139
00:12:00,320 --> 00:12:02,834
And you're sure
your husband won't wake up?

140
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:05,838
l mean, l have seen
what he does to iron bars.

141
00:12:05,960 --> 00:12:08,554
Nothing wakes Peter up.

142
00:12:08,680 --> 00:12:11,831
Certainly not the sound
of two people moaning.

143
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:27,229
Oh, you...! Thank God
l saw you come in here!

144
00:12:27,360 --> 00:12:29,954
- Rat! You rat!
- (clown) lrmy!

145
00:12:30,080 --> 00:12:33,550
You said you were going to Danzig!
You were supposed to go to Danzig!

146
00:12:33,680 --> 00:12:35,830
- Sh! My husband.
- Damn you!

147
00:12:36,840 --> 00:12:40,150
- Wait! We were talking about acrobatics!
- Acrobatics!

148
00:12:40,280 --> 00:12:42,271
l was showing him how to do a backbend.

149
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:46,188
You never take your eyes off her. You're
always standing under her trapeze,...

150
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:48,276
..looking up her legs. l see you!

151
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:51,153
- Because we're planning this routine.
- Sure you are!

152
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:55,876
What do you take me for anyway?
And l wanted to have a baby with you.

153
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:58,355
l know. We'll continue this later.

154
00:12:58,480 --> 00:13:01,677
- l know, but l don't wanna have a baby.
- You are such a pig!

155
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:04,030
- l told you...
- You are a pig.

156
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:07,709
- l told you a thousand times.
- l don't want a baby with you anyway.

157
00:13:07,840 --> 00:13:11,116
lf you were the last man on earth,
l don't want a baby with you.

158
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:12,195
Good!

159
00:13:12,320 --> 00:13:14,629
You're never gonna have to see me again!

160
00:13:14,760 --> 00:13:17,479
Good! Good riddance!

161
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:19,556
l like my freedom.

162
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:28,188
- What do you want, Kleinman?
- Doctor, l'm sorry.

163
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:32,871
Can l come in, just for a minute?
Would it be possible? l have a question.

164
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:36,838
- (Kleinman) Are you in on the plan?
- Of course l am.

165
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:41,158
- Didn't you think l would be?
- l wanna find out my assignment.

166
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:45,159
- Please, don't disturb anything.
- No, l wouldn't think of it.

167
00:13:45,280 --> 00:13:49,478
l just wanna find out my participation
in the plan, you know.

168
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:52,068
Of course, l wouldn't mind
having a little drink.

169
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:55,351
- A drink?
- You know, the fog. lt's a little damp.

170
00:13:55,480 --> 00:13:57,755
So l, you know...

171
00:13:57,880 --> 00:14:00,758
But not if it's an imposition.

172
00:14:00,880 --> 00:14:04,509
l've never been here before.
This is an interesting...

173
00:14:07,320 --> 00:14:09,276
lt's cheerful.

174
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:12,836
l'm performing an unusual amount
of autopsies these days.

175
00:14:12,960 --> 00:14:16,157
Yes, l'm sure. That's probably
what accounts for...

176
00:14:16,280 --> 00:14:20,558
..so many of those human fingers lying
around. You don't generally see that.

177
00:14:20,680 --> 00:14:24,992
l guess the maid doesn't get in
that often to straighten up, so...

178
00:14:25,120 --> 00:14:30,194
My interest in all this murder business
is entirely scientific.

179
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:32,276
l'm sure, l'm sure.

180
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:38,589
l'm determined to use this opportunity
to find out something definitive about...

181
00:14:38,720 --> 00:14:41,075
..the nature of evil.

182
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:46,558
(doctor) Why is the killer the way he is?

183
00:14:46,680 --> 00:14:50,719
Sometimes certain impulses that
can drive an insane man to murder...

184
00:14:50,840 --> 00:14:54,196
..inspire others to highly creative ends.

185
00:14:54,320 --> 00:14:57,869
Once l have him here, on this table,...

186
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:04,155
..dismembered and scrutinised
in minute detail,...

187
00:15:04,960 --> 00:15:07,793
..l shall know the answer
with certainty to questions...

188
00:15:07,920 --> 00:15:11,071
..that now l can only speculate on.

189
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:14,431
Yeah, but it's not possible
that under the microscope...

190
00:15:14,560 --> 00:15:16,869
..there's something
that you could never see?

191
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:21,039
What are you implying?
A spiritual element?

192
00:15:21,160 --> 00:15:24,118
A soul that lives on after we're dead?

193
00:15:25,640 --> 00:15:27,596
A god?

194
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:34,160
Ask him if there's anything else.

195
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:38,475
What are you thinking now?

196
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:43,469
l just must remember next time
l go out to a restaurant...

197
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:46,160
..not to order the sweetbreads.

198
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:49,150
Kleinman, you'd better go.

199
00:15:49,280 --> 00:15:51,919
The time is growing very short.

200
00:15:52,040 --> 00:15:56,397
So there's nothing you can tell me
about my participation in the plan?

201
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:01,676
l'll go.

202
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:14,078
The doctor was no help at all.

203
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:17,556
This is ridiculous. Where is everybody?

204
00:16:19,120 --> 00:16:21,680
Unless... this is part of the plan.

205
00:16:22,720 --> 00:16:25,951
Maybe they have me under surveillance.

206
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:29,789
lf anything bad happens,
they'll come running out and grab me.

207
00:16:29,920 --> 00:16:32,275
Unless they don´t come running out.

208
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:36,518
But they could never think
that l'd be any match for a maniac.

209
00:16:36,640 --> 00:16:42,033
A deranged person is supposed
to have the strength of ten men.

210
00:16:42,160 --> 00:16:45,675
l have the strength of... one small boy...

211
00:16:45,800 --> 00:16:47,756
..with polio.

212
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:50,391
Quiet, quiet, quiet!

213
00:16:50,520 --> 00:16:53,193
lt's Bretschneider. He's been strangled.

214
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:54,275
Sh!

215
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:56,755
The killer may still be near.

216
00:17:21,360 --> 00:17:23,749
(Kleinman) Poor Bretschneider.

217
00:17:23,880 --> 00:17:25,836
He had no enemies.

218
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:43,676
- (coughing)
- (gasps)

219
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:47,673
- (woman) Don't be afraid.
- Oh!

220
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:53,796
- l'm sorry l scared you.
- Oh, you... you really did scare me.

221
00:17:53,920 --> 00:17:57,435
l didn't see you
standing there in the shadows.

222
00:17:57,560 --> 00:18:00,358
lt's such a foggy night.

223
00:18:00,480 --> 00:18:02,835
l was just going into town.

224
00:18:04,760 --> 00:18:08,639
You should be indoors. lt's not safe.

225
00:18:08,760 --> 00:18:11,115
- (smashing glass)
- l don't care.

226
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:15,109
What was that?

227
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:17,196
l don't know.

228
00:18:20,280 --> 00:18:22,510
What are you doing out here tonight?

229
00:18:22,640 --> 00:18:26,189
l'm used to the streets.
lt's how l make my living.

230
00:18:27,680 --> 00:18:29,318
Oh.

