463
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:36,151
- l'm the sword-swallower.
- l didn't recognise you.

464
00:34:36,280 --> 00:34:38,953
- You look completely different.
- l know.

465
00:34:39,080 --> 00:34:42,197
l wear a beautiful costume
and my hair is different.

466
00:34:42,320 --> 00:34:45,710
l went to see Almstead the magician
because he's a favourite of mine.

467
00:34:45,840 --> 00:34:49,230
l'm an amateur magician myself.
Just something l do in my spare time.

468
00:34:49,360 --> 00:34:53,353
- l idolise him. He's a great artist.
- Yeah, he's an artist... when he's sober.

469
00:34:53,480 --> 00:34:56,278
- Well, you know...
- ls there a hotel around here?

470
00:34:56,400 --> 00:34:59,710
- l had a fight with my boyfriend.
- lt's late.

471
00:34:59,840 --> 00:35:02,718
So when you have the sword
down your throat,...

472
00:35:02,840 --> 00:35:05,115
..what happens if you get hiccups?

473
00:35:16,160 --> 00:35:19,197
Jesus. l don't know my way
around this part of town.

474
00:35:19,320 --> 00:35:23,393
l don't think there's gonna be
a hotel open at this hour.

475
00:35:23,520 --> 00:35:26,193
l'll wake up my fiancée
and you could sleep on the sofa.

476
00:35:26,320 --> 00:35:29,118
- l don't wanna wake anyone up.
- She would be glad to.

477
00:35:29,240 --> 00:35:31,708
You know, it's... it's so foggy.

478
00:35:31,840 --> 00:35:34,195
He strikes in the fog, you know.

479
00:35:35,800 --> 00:35:38,997
- You didn't hear anything, did you?
- You're so tense.

480
00:35:39,120 --> 00:35:43,238
Well, l'm usually in bed,
you know, this time of night.

481
00:35:43,360 --> 00:35:46,875
What would you do if you came
face to face with the killer?

482
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:48,956
l'd throw pepper in his eyes.

483
00:35:49,080 --> 00:35:52,436
My landlady put
some pepper in my pocket.

484
00:35:52,560 --> 00:35:55,791
- l think l could handle myself.
- Kleinman!

485
00:35:55,920 --> 00:35:59,310
- What are you doing here?
- Oh, my God! You scared me.

486
00:35:59,440 --> 00:36:02,238
- Who is she?
- She's just a friend.

487
00:36:02,360 --> 00:36:06,319
- Do you happen to know my assignment?
- Who gave you permission to socialise?

488
00:36:06,440 --> 00:36:10,592
l'm not socialising. Maybe
you recognise her. She's with the circus.

489
00:36:10,720 --> 00:36:12,676
She's the sword-swallower.

490
00:36:12,800 --> 00:36:15,633
She's unescorted.
l was just walking next to her.

491
00:36:15,760 --> 00:36:19,355
- We're getting closer to the zero hour.
- Yeah? So what do l do?

492
00:36:19,480 --> 00:36:21,675
- Don't you know?
- No. That's the point.

493
00:36:21,800 --> 00:36:24,553
You got me up, and no one's told me
what l'm supposed to do.

494
00:36:24,680 --> 00:36:28,593
l swear, if anyone is killed or hurt
as a result of your incompetence...

495
00:36:28,720 --> 00:36:31,871
l don't know enough to be incompetent.
They don't tell me what...

496
00:36:32,000 --> 00:36:36,755
Don't make a noise, and listen to me.
There is someone lurking up the alley.

497
00:36:37,640 --> 00:36:39,073
Well...

498
00:36:39,200 --> 00:36:43,432
Shall l just start weeping or would
you like me to break into a run?

499
00:36:43,560 --> 00:36:46,552
- We can trap whoever it is.
- No! l don't wanna trap anybody.

500
00:36:46,680 --> 00:36:48,716
We'll get reinforcements.

501
00:36:48,840 --> 00:36:51,195
What they say about you isn't true, is it?

502
00:36:51,320 --> 00:36:55,677
You're not really a coward
or a worm or a yellow-belly?

503
00:36:56,440 --> 00:37:00,558
No, but keep going.
You're in the right column.

504
00:37:00,680 --> 00:37:03,240
l'll circle around the block.
You head up the alley.

505
00:37:03,360 --> 00:37:06,511
- l don't wanna do this. This is trouble.
- l can go with you.

506
00:37:06,640 --> 00:37:10,076
No! She's gonna go with me! What good
are you? You're a small woman.

507
00:37:10,200 --> 00:37:11,838
l'm OK.

508
00:37:11,960 --> 00:37:16,476
You go first. lt'll throw
his timing off if he sees a body.

509
00:37:16,600 --> 00:37:21,037
Go on, Kleinman. lt'll take me a moment
or two to get round the other side.

510
00:37:25,960 --> 00:37:27,916
(Kleinman) Keep ahead of me.

511
00:37:31,760 --> 00:37:32,954
(lrmy) Sh!

512
00:37:33,080 --> 00:37:35,116
Those are my knees knocking.

513
00:37:37,920 --> 00:37:40,673
Stay calm. The trick is not to show fear.

514
00:37:51,520 --> 00:37:53,909
(lrmy) There he is! Look!

515
00:37:54,040 --> 00:37:56,315
Grab him! Grab him!

516
00:37:56,440 --> 00:37:58,396
(dog barks)

517
00:38:02,360 --> 00:38:04,157
- Kleinman!
- Mr Paulsen!

518
00:38:04,280 --> 00:38:06,510
- You know him?
- This is my boss.

519
00:38:06,640 --> 00:38:09,154
- What are you doing?
- l'm part of the plan, Your Grace.

520
00:38:09,280 --> 00:38:11,350
- Why did you attack me?
- l thought...

521
00:38:11,480 --> 00:38:15,189
- ''Thought''? Since when do you think?
- Yes, you're right, Your Majesty.

522
00:38:15,320 --> 00:38:19,552
l had a suspicion you were incompetent,
hiding behind your co-workers.

523
00:38:19,680 --> 00:38:23,832
Don't let him talk to you like that! He was
peeping at that woman getting undressed!

524
00:38:23,960 --> 00:38:26,235
- How dare you!
- Don't listen to her, sir.

525
00:38:26,360 --> 00:38:29,875
- She's swallowed sharp objects.
- Don't be a doormat for a Peeping Tom.

526
00:38:30,000 --> 00:38:32,594
- This is my boss.
- To think that l was undecided...

527
00:38:32,720 --> 00:38:37,157
- ..about your abilities versus Simon Carr.
- What can l say? You looked dangerous.

528
00:38:37,280 --> 00:38:41,034
- l didn't know you were peeping.
- What about your function in the plan?

529
00:38:41,160 --> 00:38:44,311
- l don't know my function.
- You unreliable simpleton!

530
00:38:44,440 --> 00:38:46,635
- Don't call him a simpleton.
- lt was well put.

531
00:38:46,760 --> 00:38:49,911
- You're a disgusting old man!
- No, don't say that. Go away, Miss.

532
00:38:50,040 --> 00:38:53,157
Whoever you are, go away.
Go away, go away. Leave us alone.

533
00:38:53,280 --> 00:38:58,229
Paulsen? You gave us quite a scare. l sent
Kleinman round here to check you out.

534
00:38:58,360 --> 00:39:00,316
He was just looking in the window.

535
00:39:00,440 --> 00:39:03,750
- Mark my words: he'll be a detriment.
- No, sir. Don't say that.

536
00:39:03,880 --> 00:39:06,678
- Let me block your hat.
- Give me that!

537
00:39:06,800 --> 00:39:10,713
He's always been a liability with my firm.
l'm only just beginning to realise it.

538
00:39:10,840 --> 00:39:13,479
Mr Paulsen, l didn't mean it! You...

539
00:39:13,600 --> 00:39:15,352
Sir!

540
00:39:16,520 --> 00:39:18,476
(clown) lrmy!

541
00:39:25,560 --> 00:39:27,596
lrmy!

542
00:39:41,600 --> 00:39:44,558
- We're closing.
- Just one beer? Please?

543
00:39:55,080 --> 00:39:59,596
Did anyone see a blonde woman
wandering around alone?

544
00:39:59,720 --> 00:40:01,790
Short hair?

545
00:40:01,920 --> 00:40:05,549
Oh, mercy. We never know
when we have a good thing.

546
00:40:05,680 --> 00:40:08,114
We always have to ruin it.

547
00:40:08,240 --> 00:40:10,993
l know exactly how you feel.

548
00:40:11,120 --> 00:40:13,953
The earthly paradise known as woman.

549
00:40:14,080 --> 00:40:16,435
All we'll ever know of heaven.

550
00:40:18,320 --> 00:40:20,675
All we need know of hell.

551
00:40:22,120 --> 00:40:25,192
l made love to a woman tonight
that was sheer perfection.

552
00:40:25,320 --> 00:40:30,110
lt was in a brothel, but somehow this one
didn't have that used, jaded quality.

553
00:40:30,240 --> 00:40:34,597
l never do it with whores.
You start out with a burning desire...

554
00:40:34,720 --> 00:40:39,350
..and end up the next day with a burning
sensation, if you know what l mean.

555
00:40:39,480 --> 00:40:42,756
Yes, but this one was so irresistible.

556
00:40:42,880 --> 00:40:45,348
Sweet and innocent.

557
00:40:45,480 --> 00:40:48,631
But under the sheets... a tigress.

558
00:40:49,600 --> 00:40:54,355
A violent, screaming,
passionate jungle cat.

559
00:40:55,440 --> 00:40:58,193
- You mean a good actress.
- She swore not.

560
00:40:59,800 --> 00:41:03,554
Well, you're very young,
my friend. Very naive.

561
00:41:03,680 --> 00:41:06,353
- She dug her nails into my back.
- l'm sure.

562
00:41:06,480 --> 00:41:08,710
And then she yelled ''Don't stop!''

563
00:41:08,840 --> 00:41:12,435
Yes. And stuck her tongue
inside my mouth and wiggled it around.

564
00:41:12,560 --> 00:41:15,677
l'm sure it was well worth the $20.

565
00:41:15,800 --> 00:41:18,519
20? l paid her 700.

566
00:41:18,640 --> 00:41:21,313
Yeah. Yeah, sure. Tell me another one.

567
00:41:21,440 --> 00:41:25,194
l'm afraid you've never
made love with a sword-swallower.

568
00:41:27,280 --> 00:41:29,236
l beg your pardon?

569
00:41:31,040 --> 00:41:36,068
She claims she never took money before.
lf she was acting, she should win a prize.

570
00:41:36,200 --> 00:41:40,273
lt's true l put on a heroic performance,
if l do say so myself.

571
00:41:40,400 --> 00:41:42,470
She brought out the stallion in me.

572
00:41:42,600 --> 00:41:46,070
And when she said she loved it,
l believe she was sincere.

573
00:41:46,200 --> 00:41:50,113
l think she's got a lover who doesn't
service her too well, you know?

574
00:41:50,240 --> 00:41:52,435
Some poor clown.

575
00:41:52,560 --> 00:41:55,438
But l showed her
what a good one felt like.

576
00:41:58,560 --> 00:42:01,950
What's wrong? You look incredulous.

577
00:42:02,080 --> 00:42:05,595
l swear, the dirtier l got,
the more she screamed.

578
00:42:05,720 --> 00:42:10,475
l gave her the best time she's had
in years, and l believe she loved it.

579
00:42:10,600 --> 00:42:13,797
Not that l have any further
urge for her, you know.

580
00:42:13,920 --> 00:42:17,071
The difference between
love and lust, l guess.

581
00:42:19,920 --> 00:42:24,072
When my friend wakes up,
tell him l went back to Felice's.

582
00:42:24,800 --> 00:42:27,109
This is crazy. Can't l talk you out of it?

583
00:42:27,240 --> 00:42:30,516
No, l don't want it.
l want the church to have it, all of it.

584
00:42:30,640 --> 00:42:35,668
- But you're talking about $700.
- $650. l had to pay a fine.

585
00:42:35,800 --> 00:42:38,109
But it's your money.

586
00:42:38,240 --> 00:42:41,471
- Why give it away?
- Because l'm ashamed of the way l got it.

587
00:42:41,600 --> 00:42:46,469
- Listen, l'm sure you didn't steal it.
- No. l slept with somebody for it.

588
00:42:47,880 --> 00:42:50,872
Just one person.
Does that make me a whore?

589
00:42:51,000 --> 00:42:53,389
Well, only by the dictionary definition.

590
00:42:53,520 --> 00:42:58,310
- Anyway, l'm giving it to the church.
- Yeah, but that seems so silly.

591
00:42:58,440 --> 00:43:02,035
lt's work, you know.
l'm sure you didn't do it for fun.

592
00:43:02,160 --> 00:43:05,516
No. But you know something?
lt turned out to be fun.

593
00:43:06,560 --> 00:43:11,429
Here. Would you take it in there for me
and give it to them? For the poor.

594
00:43:11,560 --> 00:43:14,597
l just can't bring myself
to go in there tonight.

595
00:43:14,720 --> 00:43:17,075
Please? Come on.

596
00:43:23,520 --> 00:43:26,751
- Yes?
- l just need a minute of your time.

597
00:43:26,880 --> 00:43:29,599
l think you can see that we're busy.

598
00:43:29,720 --> 00:43:33,599
- l just... Just for one...
- Put Kramer's name on the list.

599
00:43:33,720 --> 00:43:36,871
Have you seen his sketches
and his photo studies?

600
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:40,037
Just for a minute,
if l might have your attention...

601
00:43:40,160 --> 00:43:42,720
Didn't you hear him say we're busy?

602
00:43:44,200 --> 00:43:47,158
- Are you Kleinman?
- Yes. Yes, l am. Yes.

603
00:43:49,040 --> 00:43:50,996
Don't forget.

604
00:43:53,280 --> 00:43:55,396
Why is he putting my name on the list?

605
00:43:55,520 --> 00:43:59,069
- You've been warned twice now.
- What is this list? Might l just ask?

606
00:43:59,200 --> 00:44:01,919
- l have a donation to make.
- The poor box is in the front.

607
00:44:02,040 --> 00:44:04,315
No, this doesn't fit in the poor box.

608
00:44:04,440 --> 00:44:08,991
- Kleinman, you want me to take you in?
- No, no, no. l have $650.

609
00:44:09,120 --> 00:44:12,112
- $650.
- lt's not stolen. He thinks it's stolen.

610
00:44:12,240 --> 00:44:15,994
- Where did you get it?
- My friend said l should donate it.

611
00:44:16,120 --> 00:44:19,351
- Where did your friend get it?
- We don't have to pry excessively.

612
00:44:19,480 --> 00:44:22,677
We humbly accept this token
from the faithful.

613
00:44:22,800 --> 00:44:25,951
And l think that we know
how to show gratitude...

614
00:44:26,080 --> 00:44:29,038
..when someone performs
an act of charity.

615
00:44:35,640 --> 00:44:37,790
(priest) Manna for the poor.

616
00:44:39,000 --> 00:44:42,549
- (lrmy) Did you do it?
- (Kleinman) Yeah, l took care of it.

617
00:44:43,440 --> 00:44:45,795
- l feel so much better now.
- Good.

618
00:44:45,920 --> 00:44:47,512
Are you a religious person?

619
00:44:47,640 --> 00:44:50,916
Me? No, l'm not. You're
the second person tonight to ask that.

620
00:44:51,040 --> 00:44:53,474
The doctor - may he rest in peace -
wanted to know.

621
00:44:53,600 --> 00:44:55,989
- Do you pray ever?
- No.

622
00:44:56,120 --> 00:44:59,510
My people pray in a different language,
so l never understood.

623
00:44:59,640 --> 00:45:02,677
For all l know, they were
requesting their own troubles.

624
00:45:02,800 --> 00:45:04,950
- (baby crying)
- (woman) Help me.

625
00:45:06,280 --> 00:45:08,430
Please help me.

626
00:45:08,800 --> 00:45:10,518
- Help.
- (lrmy) Are you all right?

627
00:45:10,640 --> 00:45:13,757
- (Kleinman) Who is that?
- l'm hungry.

628
00:45:13,880 --> 00:45:16,235
l need to buy food and milk.

629
00:45:18,560 --> 00:45:20,516
My husband is dead.

630
00:45:21,520 --> 00:45:23,954
- l'm alone.
- We're friends.

631
00:45:24,080 --> 00:45:26,719
You know, you're among friends.

632
00:45:26,840 --> 00:45:29,115
Go back and get some of the money back.

633
00:45:29,240 --> 00:45:32,357
- What are you talking about?
- l want her to have half of it.

634
00:45:32,480 --> 00:45:36,792
- l can't. l just gave them the money.
- So what? Just ask for half back.

635
00:45:36,920 --> 00:45:40,037
You just gave it to them.
They give it to the poor, don't they?

636
00:45:40,160 --> 00:45:43,118
Well, theoretically they do,
but a lot of it is used...

637
00:45:43,240 --> 00:45:46,676
..to buy costumes
and velvet pillows and stuff.

638
00:45:46,800 --> 00:45:48,756
Please.

639
00:45:50,040 --> 00:45:52,395
My friend asked me
if l could possibly come...

640
00:45:52,520 --> 00:45:58,152
..and just have half the money back
that l gave you. Just $300. lt would...

641
00:45:58,280 --> 00:46:00,236
Thank you.

642
00:46:01,200 --> 00:46:05,478
Kleinman. ls that with an ''ei'' or an ''ie''?

643
00:46:05,600 --> 00:46:07,556
Put a circle around it.

644
00:46:11,520 --> 00:46:14,273
Eve. Eve, open up.

645
00:46:14,400 --> 00:46:16,231
lt's Kleinman.

646
00:46:16,360 --> 00:46:18,749
Eve. Eve, it's an emergency.

647
00:46:18,880 --> 00:46:21,678
- lt's me. lt's Max.
- (lrmy) This is a bad idea.

648
00:46:21,800 --> 00:46:24,678
No, she's a wonderful girl.
Very intelligent.

649
00:46:24,800 --> 00:46:25,755
Eve!

650
00:46:26,280 --> 00:46:28,077
Eve!

651
00:46:28,200 --> 00:46:30,794
What are doing here at this hour?
Who is this?

652
00:46:30,920 --> 00:46:33,639
- Can we come in?
- What's going on?

653
00:46:33,760 --> 00:46:36,320
She's a friend of mine.
She has no place to sleep.

654
00:46:36,440 --> 00:46:39,910
- l told her she could sleep on your sofa.
- You did?

655
00:46:40,040 --> 00:46:43,749
(lrmy) We're sorry. lt's much
too much of an imposition.

656
00:46:43,880 --> 00:46:46,314
You dare to wake me out of a deep sleep...

657
00:46:46,440 --> 00:46:49,910
..so that some complete stranger
can sleep on my sofa?

658
00:46:50,040 --> 00:46:53,237
She's not a complete stranger.
She's a friend.

659
00:46:53,360 --> 00:46:55,476
Eve, l personally vouch for her.

660
00:46:55,600 --> 00:46:58,239
l apologise, Miss.

661
00:46:58,360 --> 00:47:01,079
- Kleinman, have you been drinking?
- Have l been...?

662
00:47:01,200 --> 00:47:04,875
- When do l ever drink?
- Since when is she your friend?

663
00:47:05,000 --> 00:47:07,958
Since tonight. l met her
at the police headquarters.

664
00:47:08,080 --> 00:47:10,719
They brought her in
when they raided the brothel.

665
00:47:10,840 --> 00:47:15,914
lt's not what it sounds like. Everybody
makes one mistake now and then.

666
00:47:16,040 --> 00:47:18,315
Kleinman, what are you
doing out at this hour?

667
00:47:18,440 --> 00:47:21,716
l'm part of a vigilante committee
to help catch the maniac.

668
00:47:21,840 --> 00:47:23,956
By doing what?

669
00:47:24,080 --> 00:47:26,036
l don't exactly know.

670
00:47:27,160 --> 00:47:30,516
Go home, Kleinman.
And take your friend with you.

671
00:47:31,480 --> 00:47:35,234
You've got some nerve.
We'll discuss this in the morning.

672
00:47:40,520 --> 00:47:43,353
(Kleinman) Boy, Eve is a cold fish.

673
00:47:43,480 --> 00:47:45,596
There. l said it.

674
00:47:45,720 --> 00:47:49,759
(lrmy) ls it hard for you to admit
certain things to yourself?

675
00:47:49,880 --> 00:47:54,351
Usually it is, yes.
But for some reason tonight is different.

676
00:47:54,480 --> 00:47:58,109
You know, it's a strange feeling
to be up at this hour.

677
00:47:58,240 --> 00:48:01,471
The city is so odd
when everybody's asleep.

678
00:48:01,600 --> 00:48:05,036
lt's like a different place completely.
There's no civilisation.

679
00:48:05,160 --> 00:48:08,118
The stores are closed.
You know, it's so free.

680
00:48:09,560 --> 00:48:11,994
lt's an odd feeling for me.

681
00:48:12,120 --> 00:48:16,671
l feel l could run down the street
naked and nobody would...

682
00:48:16,800 --> 00:48:20,236
(lrmy) lt has a really free feeling.

683
00:48:20,360 --> 00:48:23,830
(Kleinman) l've never seen it from
up here, never taken the time to look.

684
00:48:23,960 --> 00:48:27,032
lt's so pretty. Some of the stars
are beginning to come up.

685
00:48:27,160 --> 00:48:30,197
The fog is just breaking a tiny bit.

686
00:48:30,680 --> 00:48:34,150
(lrmy) You see that very bright star
up in that direction?

687
00:48:34,280 --> 00:48:35,315
Mm-hm.

688
00:48:35,440 --> 00:48:39,399
For all we know, that star could have
disappeared a million years ago,...

689
00:48:39,520 --> 00:48:44,355
..and it's taken the light from it
a million years to reach us.

690
00:48:44,480 --> 00:48:47,472
So what are you saying?
That star is not there?

691
00:48:47,600 --> 00:48:49,556
That it might not be there.

692
00:48:49,680 --> 00:48:51,750
Even though l can see it
with my own eyes?

693
00:48:51,880 --> 00:48:53,836
That's right.

694
00:48:54,880 --> 00:48:57,872
That's a very disquieting thought,
you know.

695
00:48:58,000 --> 00:49:01,356
When l see something,
l like to know that it's actually there.

696
00:49:01,480 --> 00:49:05,439
Otherwise a person could sit down
in a chair and break his neck.

697
00:49:05,560 --> 00:49:08,950
You have to be able to rely on things.
lt's very important.

698
00:49:09,080 --> 00:49:11,753
You know who has these thoughts?
Schultz the tailor.

699
00:49:11,880 --> 00:49:13,871
He thinks nothing is real at all,...

700
00:49:14,000 --> 00:49:17,754
..and that everything exists
only in the dream of a dog.

701
00:49:17,880 --> 00:49:20,110
But this is real, isn't it?

702
00:49:20,240 --> 00:49:23,596
And beautiful.
Just think about it for a minute.

703
00:49:23,720 --> 00:49:27,679
Here we are, we're two strangers,
and we're out in the night, and it's just...

704
00:49:27,800 --> 00:49:30,268
..so peaceful and quiet.

705
00:49:30,400 --> 00:49:35,838
Suddenly there's a little clearing in the fog
and we can see right out to the stars.

706
00:49:35,960 --> 00:49:39,839
Doesn't this moment just seem perfect?

707
00:49:39,960 --> 00:49:44,476
Yes, but, you know,
it... it... passes so quickly.

708
00:49:44,600 --> 00:49:47,637
Look. Even now the fog
is starting to go back in.

709
00:49:47,760 --> 00:49:50,672
Everything's always moving all the time.

710
00:49:50,800 --> 00:49:55,430
Everything's constantly in motion,
so it's no wonder that l'm nauseous.

711
00:49:55,560 --> 00:50:00,315
My father used to say
''We're all happy if we only knew it.''

712
00:50:03,640 --> 00:50:06,598
Kleinman! We've been
looking all over for you.

713
00:50:06,720 --> 00:50:11,157
l've been wandering around in the fog. l'm
waiting for Hacker to tell me what to do.

714
00:50:11,280 --> 00:50:14,477
- Hacker's dead.
- The killer got Hacker?

715
00:50:14,600 --> 00:50:18,991
- Hacker wasn't murdered by the maniac.
- Well, who then?

716
00:50:19,120 --> 00:50:22,874
- Someone from the other faction.
- Since when did we have other factions?

717
00:50:23,000 --> 00:50:25,833
People have their own ideas
about how to achieve results.

718
00:50:25,960 --> 00:50:29,316
Naturally, there's tension.
Miller formed his own group.

719
00:50:29,440 --> 00:50:32,830
- But so quickly it becomes violent?
- Hacker asked for it.

720
00:50:32,960 --> 00:50:36,873
He was stubborn and hot-headed, despite
the fact that his plan wasn't working.

721
00:50:37,000 --> 00:50:39,753
You sound like you didn't
agree with him either.

722
00:50:39,880 --> 00:50:42,155
- l'm with Vogel's group.
- Who's Vogel?

723
00:50:42,280 --> 00:50:44,271
Since when is there a third group?

724
00:50:44,400 --> 00:50:46,960
There's disagreement
on how to handle things!

725
00:50:47,080 --> 00:50:49,958
The last thing we need is disagreement.
We should be...

726
00:50:50,080 --> 00:50:54,596
Don't lecture me, Kleinman!
Are you with us or against us?

727
00:50:54,720 --> 00:50:57,393
l don't know. l don't have
enough facts so l can choose.

728
00:50:57,520 --> 00:50:59,750
Now listen, Kleinman.

729
00:50:59,880 --> 00:51:02,348
Lives are at stake.
You have to make a choice!

730
00:51:02,480 --> 00:51:04,994
You can't threaten him!
Don't take this from him!

731
00:51:05,120 --> 00:51:07,270
- She's starting already.
- Who's this?

732
00:51:07,400 --> 00:51:09,516
There you are.
Where the hell have you been?

733
00:51:09,640 --> 00:51:12,393
Where have you been? You wake me
in the middle of the night.

734
00:51:12,520 --> 00:51:16,274
- Now l hear Hacker's dead.
- You wandered off when we needed you.

735
00:51:16,400 --> 00:51:20,075
- You didn't tell me anything.
- Kleinman's joined our faction.

736
00:51:20,200 --> 00:51:24,079
- ls that true, Kleinman?
- No. Look, we have to cooperate.

737
00:51:24,200 --> 00:51:27,715
- Are you with them or us?
- l don't know. How can l know?

738
00:51:27,840 --> 00:51:30,274
l don't know what the alternatives are.

739
00:51:30,400 --> 00:51:33,870
ls one apples, is one pears?
Are they both tangerines?

740
00:51:34,000 --> 00:51:36,389
Let's kill him before
he gives everything away.

741
00:51:36,520 --> 00:51:38,909
l don't know anything.
l can't give anything away.

742
00:51:39,040 --> 00:51:42,032
We're here arguing and there's
an enemy out there killing us.

743
00:51:42,160 --> 00:51:44,594
Soon we're gonna do his killing for him.

744
00:51:44,720 --> 00:51:48,713
- The murderer!
- He believes he's located the guilty party.

745
00:51:48,840 --> 00:51:51,070
lt's Spiro, the great clairvoyant.

746
00:51:51,200 --> 00:51:53,634
l've heard of him.
He's solved a lot of cases.

747
00:51:53,760 --> 00:51:56,194
They say all he needs
is something to sniff or feel.

748
00:51:56,320 --> 00:51:58,311
He's solved some kidnappings.

749
00:51:58,440 --> 00:52:01,796
Mr Spiro is on the verge
of revealing the killer.

750
00:52:06,200 --> 00:52:08,873
Mr Spiro wishes to sniff you.

751
00:52:10,600 --> 00:52:12,556
- Me?
- Yes.

752
00:52:13,600 --> 00:52:16,637
- Well, how come?
- lt's enough he wishes it.

753
00:52:16,760 --> 00:52:18,796
No! No, don't let him do it.

754
00:52:18,920 --> 00:52:22,799
Hey, wasn't that woman booked on
prostitution charges earlier tonight?

755
00:52:22,920 --> 00:52:25,673
- Come on, Kleinman.
- l don't wanna get sniffed.

756
00:52:25,800 --> 00:52:27,870
Come on!

757
00:52:28,000 --> 00:52:31,151
- l don't wanna be sniffed! No!
- Stand still.

758
00:52:31,280 --> 00:52:35,239
- Go ahead, sniff away.
- This is crazy. Why should he sniff me?

759
00:52:38,880 --> 00:52:41,155
What is this man sniffing?

760
00:52:41,280 --> 00:52:45,637
lt's probably cheese, cos tonight was the
night l changed the traps in the bedroom.

761
00:52:45,760 --> 00:52:47,671
- Frightened?
- l'm not frightened.

762
00:52:47,800 --> 00:52:51,110
This is unfair. Kleinman,
stand up for your rights!

763
00:52:51,240 --> 00:52:54,198
l know what he's sniffing.
lt's salad dressing.

764
00:52:54,320 --> 00:52:57,118
l spilled salad dressing
on myself this evening.

765
00:52:57,240 --> 00:53:01,392
My landlady cooks for me, so she made
me a nice salad with a little whitefish.

766
00:53:01,520 --> 00:53:04,114
She makes beautiful whitefish.
l can't have meat...

767
00:53:04,240 --> 00:53:07,835
- Shut up!
- This man has something in his pocket.

768
00:53:07,960 --> 00:53:10,235
Mr Spiro has done it again.

769
00:53:10,360 --> 00:53:14,114
- Look in his pocket.
- l have nothing. There's nothing.

770
00:53:14,240 --> 00:53:16,196
Check his inside pocket.

771
00:53:18,240 --> 00:53:21,391
This was stolen from
police headquarters earlier tonight.

772
00:53:21,520 --> 00:53:24,990
- This is stolen property.
- l carry a glass with me. l get thirsty.

773
00:53:25,120 --> 00:53:28,476
- l like to have, you know, occasionally...
- We've trapped him!

774
00:53:28,600 --> 00:53:30,670
Why'd you do it? You killed the doctor!

775
00:53:30,800 --> 00:53:33,394
Do what? You believe this guy
from smelling me?

776
00:53:33,520 --> 00:53:36,717
Mr Spiro's uncanny power
has never failed him yet.

777
00:53:36,840 --> 00:53:40,549
Why would l kill the doctor?
The man took out my gall bladder.

778
00:53:40,680 --> 00:53:43,558
- With my consent.
- Don't expect him to make sense.

779
00:53:43,680 --> 00:53:47,639
That's how it is with a psychopath. They
can be logical on every point except one:

780
00:53:47,760 --> 00:53:50,354
Their weakness, their point of insanity.

781
00:53:50,480 --> 00:53:54,393
- And Kleinman's always so damn logical.
- This is a joke, isn't it?

782
00:53:54,520 --> 00:53:58,593
We're all reasonable,
normal, rational people, right?

783
00:53:58,720 --> 00:54:00,517
Tell me where you got this.

784
00:54:00,640 --> 00:54:03,837
Once again l thank the Lord
for the special gift...

785
00:54:03,960 --> 00:54:06,315
..he has seen fit to bestow on me.

786
00:54:06,440 --> 00:54:09,159
l say we make an example of him.
Who has a rope?

787
00:54:09,280 --> 00:54:12,511
No, you can't do this!
Kleinman, defend yourself!

788
00:54:12,640 --> 00:54:15,234
- They're picking on me.
- How do you plead, Kleinman?

789
00:54:15,360 --> 00:54:19,638
Not guilty! l plead not guilty. l never did
anything in my life to deserve any trouble.

790
00:54:19,760 --> 00:54:23,309
- lf anything, l deserve a bonus.
- Come on! Let's get him.

791
00:54:25,320 --> 00:54:27,675
Where'd he get that pepper?

792
00:55:30,880 --> 00:55:32,836
Let me in. lt's Max.

793
00:55:33,640 --> 00:55:35,596
- Who is it?
- Max. Max.

794
00:55:36,840 --> 00:55:38,956
- Max. Let me in.
- Max?

795
00:55:39,080 --> 00:55:41,799
Yes! l have to come in. They're after me.

796
00:55:41,920 --> 00:55:42,989
Max.

797
00:55:43,120 --> 00:55:46,874
Stop staring at me. l'm not a ghost.
Not yet, although they're trying to kill me.

798
00:55:47,000 --> 00:55:48,831
- Who?
- There's a mob.

799
00:55:48,960 --> 00:55:50,951
And you dare to come here?

800
00:55:51,080 --> 00:55:55,790
What could l do? l'm running for my life,
and l saw your place and, you know, l...

801
00:55:55,920 --> 00:55:59,151
Whatever they think about you,
l'm sure you're guilty of it.

802
00:55:59,280 --> 00:56:02,750
Alma, is it possible
that l could murder somebody?

803
00:56:02,880 --> 00:56:06,111
Alma, l'm asking you a question.
lt's me, Max.

804
00:56:06,240 --> 00:56:08,800
l never wanted to lay eyes on you again.

805
00:56:08,920 --> 00:56:12,390
l know. l did a bad thing.
But time heals. lt's been years.

806
00:56:12,520 --> 00:56:15,512
The more l thought about it,
the more l wanted you dead.

807
00:56:15,640 --> 00:56:18,154
Cut in little pieces and thrown to the dogs.

808
00:56:18,280 --> 00:56:21,158
Jesus. You've given this thing
some very specific thought.

809
00:56:21,280 --> 00:56:25,478
You're the worst scum,
and l won't rest until you fry in hell.

810
00:56:25,600 --> 00:56:27,795
Can l stay here tonight? ls it...?

811
00:56:27,920 --> 00:56:30,957
How could you do it?
How could you leave me at the altar,...

812
00:56:31,080 --> 00:56:34,152
..in front of family and friends,
humiliated and weeping?

813
00:56:34,280 --> 00:56:36,999
l've explained that.
There's two sides to every story.

814
00:56:37,120 --> 00:56:39,111
Do you deny we were to be married...

815
00:56:39,240 --> 00:56:41,834
..and you made an idiot of me
in front of everyone?

816
00:56:41,960 --> 00:56:45,475
l was nervous.
l was a little drunk. l was unsure.

817
00:56:45,600 --> 00:56:48,433
- Unsure?
- lt was your idea to get married.

818
00:56:48,560 --> 00:56:52,519
- And it was your idea to get me pregnant.
- lt was a hysterical pregnancy.

819
00:56:52,640 --> 00:56:54,949
- You weren't actually pregnant.
- So what?

820
00:56:55,080 --> 00:56:58,834
- Will you keep quiet? l'm trying to hide.
- We looked everywhere.

821
00:56:58,960 --> 00:57:01,872
My father, my mother, my brothers.
''Where could he be?''

822
00:57:02,000 --> 00:57:05,310
''He was here before the ceremony.
True, he was drinking.''

823
00:57:05,440 --> 00:57:08,000
Listen, l know what you're gonna say.

824
00:57:08,120 --> 00:57:11,237
While everybody's walking around,
puzzled and muttering,...

825
00:57:11,360 --> 00:57:15,797
..sensing my discomfort,
he's discovered in a broom closet,...

826
00:57:15,920 --> 00:57:17,956
..making love with my sister.

827
00:57:18,080 --> 00:57:20,674
Jesus. l thought l explained that to you.

828
00:57:20,800 --> 00:57:23,314
What kind of explanation
could you possibly have?

829
00:57:23,440 --> 00:57:26,273
You were naked in the closet
with my sister!

830
00:57:26,400 --> 00:57:28,789
Look at her.
She still holds that against me.

831
00:57:28,920 --> 00:57:33,311
lt's not that l didn't like you. l just didn't
love you. l thought you were pregnant.

832
00:57:33,440 --> 00:57:36,671
- l was trying to do the honourable thing.
- The honourable thing?

833
00:57:36,800 --> 00:57:38,836
To desert me at the altar...

834
00:57:38,960 --> 00:57:43,909
..and make love with my younger sister
in a broom closet is the honourable thing?

835
00:57:44,040 --> 00:57:46,600
Look, we just had
your best interests at heart.

836
00:57:46,720 --> 00:57:49,109
l want you dead, and her.

837
00:57:49,240 --> 00:57:52,550
Don't. She was a wonderful girl.
She's fabulous. She loved you.

838
00:57:52,680 --> 00:57:56,389
She worshipped you like a goddess.
She was singing your praises.

839
00:57:56,520 --> 00:57:59,478
- Till the moment l slipped her pants off...
- Get out of here!

840
00:57:59,600 --> 00:58:01,989
Be careful with that. Be angry with me.

841
00:58:02,120 --> 00:58:06,193
All right, fault me. But not Trudy.
Not Trudy, l beg of you. Not your sister.

842
00:58:06,320 --> 00:58:10,029
l convinced her to do it. She didn't
wanna do it. l promised to get her steaks.

843
00:58:10,160 --> 00:58:12,993
Kleinman's here! Here he is!

844
00:58:13,120 --> 00:58:14,678
Kleinman's here!

845
00:58:14,800 --> 00:58:19,749
Get out and die! Get out! Die!
You rot in hell, you filthy vermin!

846
00:58:19,880 --> 00:58:23,429
lt's good to see you're not bitter
after all these years.

847
00:58:34,800 --> 00:58:37,519
- (screams)
- You whore!

848
00:58:37,640 --> 00:58:41,599
- l'll kill you!
- You're the one who should be ashamed!

849
00:58:41,720 --> 00:58:44,553
How could you? With a student
for a few silver coins?

850
00:58:44,680 --> 00:58:47,194
lt wasn't a few silver coins.
He gave me $700.

851
00:58:47,320 --> 00:58:50,676
- You didn't know what you were doing.
- l enjoyed myself.

852
00:58:50,800 --> 00:58:53,030
l'll kill you!

853
00:58:53,160 --> 00:58:55,833
- l hate you!
- l was drunk. l was miserable.

854
00:58:55,960 --> 00:58:58,633
l hate you! l hate you! l'll kill you!

855
00:58:58,760 --> 00:59:01,320
l wish we'd never met. Come home.

856
00:59:01,440 --> 00:59:04,557
- l never want to see you again.
- He was young and handsome.

857
00:59:04,680 --> 00:59:07,831
- Yes, he was!
- And you enjoyed yourself?

858
00:59:07,960 --> 00:59:11,509
- Was he a better lover than me?
- He treated me romantically.

859
00:59:11,640 --> 00:59:14,757
But he felt nothing! Just lust, pure lust.

860
00:59:14,880 --> 00:59:18,190
- l don't care to talk about it.
- l'm sure you don't. Where's the money?

861
00:59:18,320 --> 00:59:21,232
- l gave it to charity.
- You're joking!

862
00:59:21,360 --> 00:59:23,430
You don't think l'm worth $700?

863
00:59:23,560 --> 00:59:26,950
There isn't a whore
in the world worth $700,...

864
00:59:27,080 --> 00:59:30,038
..especially not
an amateur whore like you.

865
00:59:30,960 --> 00:59:33,076
- Bastard!
- (woman screams)

866
00:59:33,200 --> 00:59:35,156
What's that?

867
00:59:37,240 --> 00:59:40,676
- l'm scared.
- Don't panic.

868
00:59:40,800 --> 00:59:42,552
Hold me.

869
00:59:42,680 --> 00:59:44,636
l'll protect you.

870
00:59:45,440 --> 00:59:47,396
lt is rather scary.

871
00:59:53,040 --> 00:59:55,395
(clown) Oh, my God! lt's gruesome.

872
00:59:58,320 --> 01:00:00,276
- Oh, God!
- Be quiet.

873
01:00:11,000 --> 01:00:12,956
(yowling)

874
01:00:14,120 --> 01:00:15,917
(footsteps)

875
01:00:16,040 --> 01:00:17,996
- l hear footsteps.
- Quiet.

876
01:00:19,200 --> 01:00:21,156
- Listen.
- They're getting fainter.

877
01:00:21,280 --> 01:00:25,432
- Quick, we have to get out of here.
- Wait. Do you hear something?

878
01:00:29,480 --> 01:00:31,311
(baby crying)

879
01:00:31,440 --> 01:00:34,796
The same woman. The same woman l...

880
01:00:34,920 --> 01:00:38,833
l saw her earlier.
We gave her some money.

881
01:00:38,960 --> 01:00:41,315
She had a baby with her.

882
01:00:50,920 --> 01:00:54,549
- lt's too horrible to think about.
- ls she all right?

883
01:00:55,880 --> 01:00:58,235
The poor little thing.

884
01:00:59,280 --> 01:01:02,989
- We'll have to keep the baby.
- What? What are you talking about?

885
01:01:03,120 --> 01:01:05,475
- She has no one.
- What about her father?

886
01:01:05,600 --> 01:01:07,909
- No. There is none.
- How do you know?

887
01:01:08,040 --> 01:01:11,999
l talked to the woman earlier.
There's no father, there's no family.

888
01:01:12,120 --> 01:01:15,749
- She has no one. She was all alone.
- We can't keep a baby.

889
01:01:15,880 --> 01:01:18,713
- You want to just leave her in the gutter?
- No, but...

890
01:01:18,840 --> 01:01:21,229
But what? She needs parents.

891
01:01:21,360 --> 01:01:24,158
- Yes, but...
- Stop ''yes, butting'' and ''no, butting''.

892
01:01:24,280 --> 01:01:28,193
l wanted a baby.
Now God has dropped one in my lap.

893
01:01:28,320 --> 01:01:31,471
- We have no money.
- No, we do. Come here.

894
01:01:33,000 --> 01:01:35,992
Look. You just hold her for a second.

895
01:01:36,120 --> 01:01:39,874
- l can't.
- Just hold her for a second. Be careful.

896
01:01:40,640 --> 01:01:42,995
- Here. Maybe...
- (fluttering)

897
01:01:47,120 --> 01:01:49,475
Don't put her on the ground!

898
01:01:55,200 --> 01:01:56,428
Here.

899
01:01:56,560 --> 01:01:58,312
- $300.
- lt's not legal.

900
01:01:58,440 --> 01:02:02,956
- We have to give her to an orphanage.
- How are they gonna treat her?

901
01:02:03,080 --> 01:02:06,959
She needs love and care.
She needs a mother and a father.

902
01:02:07,080 --> 01:02:09,992
- lt's out of the question.
- Well, l´m gonna keep her.

903
01:02:10,120 --> 01:02:14,557
No. You're gonna put her back where
l found her, and we'll inform the police.

904
01:02:14,680 --> 01:02:17,797
- Help!
- Quiet! The killer could be lurking.

905
01:02:17,920 --> 01:02:21,276
You don't have to,
but l'm gonna raise this baby.

906
01:02:24,760 --> 01:02:26,990
She's so tiny.

907
01:02:27,120 --> 01:02:30,476
- She's pretty.
- l didn't say she wasn't pretty.

908
01:02:32,800 --> 01:02:35,155
This is madness. Madness.

909
01:02:37,440 --> 01:02:39,396
She is beautiful.

910
01:02:40,600 --> 01:02:43,558
Oh, God. Oh, God.

911
01:02:51,920 --> 01:02:53,876
He must have come down here.

